    <h2 class="h2" id="about">What are Centers?</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <div class="last-item">Centers are an interactive way for you to learn pieces of information on a particular
                        topic and normally have learning materials to help enhance the education a you will receive.</div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="h2" id="rotation">Center Rotations</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <div class="last-item">You will rotate in a clockwise pattern, this way it is consistent and as little confusion
                        as possible for you. I do this just so that way every transition can be as smooth as possible.</div>
        <img src="/static/img/center_rotation.png" />
    </div>

    <h2 class="h2" id="time">How Long Will I Be in a Center?</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <div class="last-item">Since we have about 75 minutes per class we will have about 24 minutes per center so that way
                        we have about 5 minutes left at the end of class to clean up and do our exit slip.</div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="h2" id="next">How Do I Know Where to Go Next?</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <div class="last-item">So now you know how long you will be there, the rotation pattern of centers, well what if you
                        forget? Well let us just say there will be arrows on the ground to remind you what direction
                        to go. Also on each desk there will be a table that tells you the order to go.</div>
